     [xslt]    topicZone="body">A: Yes, you may submit a complaint anonymously. The ability of the department to respond to the complaint is related to the quality and quantity of the information provided. If the department does not have the ability to make inquiries of the complainant, the allegations may be more difficult for the department to prove. While the department makes every effort to honor a complainants request for anonymity, the materials are subject to public records law. </p><p xmlns="http://reallysi.com/namespaces/generic-wordprocessing-xml"
